<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">714.18/35: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-28T17:00:00-06:00">February 28, 1935—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8. My telegram February 28, 4 p.m. I fear President Ubico will be most
                            reluctant to adopt the procedure outlined in Minister Sack’s telegram of
                            February 28, 10 a.m., but he may accept it if I am authorized to propose
                            it as the suggestion of the Secretary of State. I hope the Department
                            can send me a telegram in that sense which I can show to President
                            Ubico.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>